1
00:00:00,013 --> 00:00:03,032
nodestorm: a live canvas your agent draws on while you decide

2
00:00:03,033 --> 00:00:06,033
Claude Code (any MCP agent) proposes an architecture...

3
00:00:06,033 --> 00:00:09,037
Components become cards, dependencies become edges

4
00:00:09,037 --> 00:00:12,545
Status rails: existing, proposed - and the agent is now waiting on YOU

5
00:00:13,044 --> 00:00:16,053
Every open choice is pinned to its component

6
00:00:16,053 --> 00:00:19,181
Hover an option - the components it would ripple into light up

7
00:00:19,181 --> 00:00:21,696
Picked - with the trade-offs recorded

8
00:00:21,696 --> 00:00:24,698
Add a note for the agent and send your decisions

9
00:00:24,698 --> 00:00:27,705
The agent wakes with your decisions and updates the graph

10
00:00:27,833 --> 00:00:30,968
The canvas is yours too - add your own components

11
00:00:30,968 --> 00:00:33,971
Rename, connect, delete - your edits flow back to the agent

12
00:00:33,971 --> 00:00:36,977
Deleting an agent's component asks the agent politely

13
00:00:36,977 --> 00:00:39,477
Undo covers every edit until decisions are delivered

14
00:00:39,500 --> 00:00:44,528
The minimap pans big graphs - groups collapse into one card

15
00:00:44,528 --> 00:00:47,536
Search highlights matches...

16
00:00:47,536 --> 00:00:50,536
...and Enter zoom-cycles through them

17
00:00:50,044 --> 00:00:53,548
Sessions are parallel brainstorms - agents can wait on one while you work in another

18
00:00:53,548 --> 00:00:56,553
Compare shows how two sessions drifted

19
00:00:56,553 --> 00:00:59,197
The timeline is the session's full decision log

20
00:01:00,055 --> 00:01:03,235
Export writes a Markdown decision record - pros, cons, and the trail

21
00:01:04,058 --> 00:01:12,294
Twelve palettes, light and dark, live-switching

22
00:01:12,301 --> 00:01:15,301
Narrow window? The bar folds - message the agent from the compose pod

23
00:01:15,200 --> 00:01:18,260
Even tiny windows keep every control reachable via More

